    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that \"meaning\" you're talking about feels so forced. it's just a coping mechanism to distract us from the fact that we're just biological accidents on a rock that's eventually going to be gone. it feels like we're just performing for an audience that isn't there. it's exhausting to keep up the act when you know the math doesn't add up to anything in the end.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
